{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Magnetometer.z","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer/z","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor_APIs\">Sensor APIs</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer/x\"><code>x</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer/y\"><code>y</code></a></li><li><em><code>z</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Sensor API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor\"><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AmbientLightSensor\"><code>AmbientLightSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GravitySensor\"><code>GravitySensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gyroscope\"><code>Gyroscope</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RelativeOrientationSensor\"><code>RelativeOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SensorErrorEvent\"><code>SensorErrorEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>z</code></strong> read-only property of the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer</code></a> interface returns a double-precision integer containing\n  the magnetic field around the device's z axis.\n</p>\n<p>\n  If a feature policy blocks use of a feature it is because your code is inconsistent\n  with the policies set on your server. This is not something that would ever be shown to\n  a user. The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy\"><code>Feature-Policy</code></a> HTTP header article contains implementation\n  instructions.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The magnetometer is typically read in the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/reading_event\" title=\"reading\"><code>reading</code></a> event\n  callback. In the example below this occurs sixty times a second.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> magSensor <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Magnetometer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">frequency</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">60</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nmagSensor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'reading'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token parameter\">e</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Magnetic field along the X-axis \"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> magSensor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>x<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Magnetic field along the Y-axis \"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> magSensor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>y<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Magnetic field along the Z-axis \"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> magSensor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>z<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nmagSensor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">start</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/magnetometer/#magnetometer-z","title":"Magnetometer"}],"query":"api.Magnetometer.z"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Magnetometer.z","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer/z/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The z read-only property of the\n  Magnetometer interface returns a double-precision integer containing\n  the magnetic field around the device's z axis.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-06-01T05:12:48.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/magnetometer/z","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/magnetometer/z/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/c1f8207fa145db27da55bf832c85a63aeb7d24b7","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer","title":"Magnetometer"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer/z","title":"Magnetometer.z"}],"pageTitle":"Magnetometer.z - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}